sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Validation Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>SA Token Auth
    participant Scheduler as K8s/Volcano Scheduler
    participant MasterPod as Master Pod<br/>23456/TCP
    participant WorkerPod as Worker Pod<br/>23456/TCP
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Storage as S3/Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 1: Training Job Creation and Execution

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f pytorchjob.yaml<br/>User credentials (kubeconfig)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>HTTPS/9443 mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Response (Accept/Reject)
    K8sAPI-->>User: PyTorchJob Created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch PyTorchJob CRD<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: New PyTorchJob Event

    alt Gang Scheduling Enabled
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+
        Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Watch PodGroup<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    end

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pods (Master + Workers)<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Services (Headless)<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+

    alt Gang Scheduling
        Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Bind All Pods Together<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    else Normal Scheduling
        K8sAPI->>MasterPod: Schedule Pod
        K8sAPI->>WorkerPod: Schedule Pods
    end

    MasterPod->>Registry: Pull training image<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Image Pull Secret
    WorkerPod->>Registry: Pull training image<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>Image Pull Secret

    Registry-->>MasterPod: Container Image
    Registry-->>WorkerPod: Container Image

    Note over MasterPod,WorkerPod: Init Containers Run (PyTorch: coordinate master selection)

    MasterPod->>Storage: Download training dataset<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>AWS IAM/Credentials
    WorkerPod->>Storage: Download training dataset<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>AWS IAM/Credentials

    Storage-->>MasterPod: Dataset
    Storage-->>WorkerPod: Dataset

    Note over MasterPod,WorkerPod: Distributed Training Communication

    WorkerPod->>MasterPod: Connect to rendezvous<br/>TCP/23456 (plaintext)
    MasterPod-->>WorkerPod: Coordinate training<br/>Framework-specific protocol

    loop Training Iterations
        WorkerPod->>MasterPod: Gradient updates<br/>TCP/23456
        MasterPod->>WorkerPod: Parameter sync<br/>TCP/23456
    end

    MasterPod->>Storage: Save model checkpoint<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+
    WorkerPod->>Storage: Save model checkpoint<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 2: Monitoring and Observability

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080 (no auth)
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Operator metrics<br/>(job counts, reconciliation time)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl get pytorchjob<br/>User credentials
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job status (Running/Succeeded/Failed)

    Note over MasterPod,WorkerPod: Training Completion

    MasterPod-->>Controller: Pod Succeeded
    WorkerPod-->>Controller: Pod Succeeded
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status=Succeeded<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+
